descriptionHtml:
OncoPower provides personalized cancer care services with specialists that you can access at any time from the comfort of your home. OncoPower Ask-a-Doc Service compliments your treating oncologist and care team


Ask-A-Doc:

Utilize our Ask-A-Doc feature to access on-demand Q&A and Live Stream services with oncologists and other health professionals.

Consult specialists on subjects such as treatment options, nutrition, mental health, financial support, and more.

Get multiple opinions on your most important questions.


Care Navigation:

Gain access through Patient Education Suites to symptom and drug-related videos recommended for you by your personal care team.

Use the Medical Storage feature to store and access or send medical records at any time.

Try out our Pill Reminder feature to easily keep track of your medication day-to-day.


Social Feed:

Find the latest studies, share videos, and interact with other patients and providers all on a single feed.


Support Groups:

Connect with other patients who share the same cancer type or oncologist while you form and manage your own support groups.


Ask-A-Doc Care:

Consult a panel of experts: medical, radiation, and surgical oncologists, pathologist, Registered Dietitian, Social Worker, Behavioral and Financial Counselors and Tumor Board.

Use on demand or Live Stream sessions to receive treatment options, wellness/nutrition, mental health, financial counseling and more.

Get multiple opinions on the most important pressing questions in your cancer treatment.


Manage Your Care:

Patient education on symptom management and treatment -specific videos recommended to you by your personal care team.

Use the Medical Storage feature to store and access or share medical records at any time.

Our Pill Reminder enables you to set reminders so you never miss a dose, achieve treatment adherence, and improve outcomes.


Social Feed and Support Group:

Find the latest studies, share videos, and interact with other patients, doctors and other providers all in a single community.

Connect with other patients who share the same cancer type or with your doctor. Form and manage your own support groups.


Security and Satisfaction Guarantee:

Site security is audited by a third party auditor. HIPAA complaint and all providers are credentialed.




OncoPower Ask-A-Doc Services come with a satisfaction guarantee. Cancel your subscription anytime and seek a refund.

OncoPower provides personalized cancer care services with specialists that you can access at any time from the comfort of your home. OncoPower augments your care team with social support, high quality information, and a whole health approach (nutrition, meditation, behavioral therapy, financial counseling, etc.).

Best cancer patient app:

“As a patient I could not ask for a better app; Patient videos, ask-a-doc, ask-a-dietitian, pill reminder, medical records and daily check in are all super helpful. But the best is the Ask-a-Doc service.” - Edid Probbingnezzl

“Oncopower remote care app is very easy to use and the videos are informative. With doctor visits, I struggle to list all the questions that I need to ask. Oncopower Ask-a-Doc is super easy to get questions clarified.” - Josalin Brithmantiuif

“I am a breast cancer patient struggling with multiple apps and sites. This app is perfect because it combines so many things that I need in one place.” - Jolane Glavismsstu


Features:

Free Tools
· Video Education Library (explains treatment options, medications, how to manage side effects, good nutrition, basics of port care, etc.)
· Registered Dietitians, Behavioral Therapists, and a Meditation Coach that are responsive
· Pill Reminder so you never miss a dose, can achieve treatment adherence, and improve outcomes
· Medical records storage with OncDrive to store and access or share medical records at any time
· Feel the support of joining a community with your peers while also having access to top professionals

OncoPower Premium
· Consult a panel of experts for individualized recommendations, specialists include Medical, Radiation, and Surgical Oncologists, Pathologist, Registered Dietitian, Social Worker, Behavioral Therapist, and Financial Counselors
· Get multiple opinions on the most important and pressing questions along your cancer treatment journey for less than the cost of a copay

Security and Satisfaction Guarantee
· Site security is audited by a third party. HIPAA complaint. All providers are credentialed.
· OncoPower Premium comes with a satisfaction guarantee. Cancel your subscription anytime.

descriptionHtml:
OncoPower is a FREE and all-in-one social and care support app for cancer patients, caregivers, advocacy organizations, and healthcare professionals. We bring together social-emotional support, clinical tools, wellness content, and high-quality evidence-based resources via the education library. We use cutting-edge AI to create a personalized experience for you. Enjoy the comfort of supportive care right from home, anytime you need it.

Featured Tools:
• Education Library has hundreds of evidence-based videos, expert interviews, audio files, and PDFs to ensure that you understand topics like treatment options and how they work, symptom and side effect management, good nutrition, wellness and physical activity, handling financial and insurance/legal challenges, and any other issues that might come up during the cancer journey. OncoPower partners with top organizations to bring you the latest and greatest information in a wide range of topic areas
• Support Groups personalized to your needs and interests
• Clinical Trials matches you to the best trials just for you, with an oncology nurse navigator on standby for all of your coordination questions
• Ask-a-Doc allows for private, personal questions to be asked to healthcare professionals (in-app subscription service, cheaper than a copay and unlimited questions)
• Daily Check-In creates a daily opportunity for reflection on how you're feeling physically and mentally that can be shared with the community or saved just for you
• Pill Reminder helps you stay on track with all medications and integrates with our Medication Savings suite, brought to you in collaboration with Mark Cuban Cost Plus Drug Company, so you can get the best price for your medications
• Meditations available and designed for all sorts of challenges that cancer patients go through, such as resilience, sleep, pain management, scan anxiety

Patients enjoy augmenting your in-person care with all of the day to day support that is needed to stay on track
Caregivers enjoy the support of the community, ask questions and learn from patients, survivors, and even professionals
Advocacy Organizations enjoy reaching targeted patients by uploading your resources and materials which are funneled efficiently to the right users
Healthcare Professionals enjoy networking, sharing case studies and recent research, and seeing dialogue among the patients (but only if you want to!)
